					<subsection>
						<title>Implication</title>
					
					<p>
					The last connective we'll consider (for now) is <em>implication</em>.
				</p>
	
				<definition xml:id="def-implications">
					<p>
						Let <m>P</m> and <m>Q</m> be statements.
						The <term>implication</term>, "<m>P</m> implies <m>Q</m>" (or "if <m>P</m>, then <m>Q</m>") is denoted <m>P\Rightarrow Q</m>, and is false only when <m>P</m> is true but <m>Q</m> is false.
						See <xref ref="table-implication" />.
					</p>
					
					<table xml:id="table-implication">
					  <title>
						The implication <m>P\Rightarrow Q</m>.
					  </title>
					  <tabular halign="center">
						<row bottom="medium">
						  <cell halign="left" right="medium">
							<m>​P</m>
						  </cell>
						  <cell halign="left" right="medium">
							<m>​Q</m>
						  </cell>
						  <cell halign="left">
							<m>P\Rightarrow Q​</m>
						  </cell>
						</row>
						<row>
						  <cell right="medium">
							T
						  </cell>
						  <cell right="medium">
							T
						  </cell>
